 emphasizing the need for female gynecologists and teachers did the women's movement carve out a niche for academic women. Because the nineteenth-century German university was the model for the modern research university, the controversy resonates with contemporary American debates surrounding multiculturalism and higher education.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362050640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503620506423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503620506/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles